---
import Legal from "../layouts/Legal.astro";
import { site } from "../config";
---

<Legal title="Privacy Policy" updated="June 2026">
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how TempoSeeker ("we", "us") handles information when
    you use the TempoSeeker iPhone app. TempoSeeker is built to keep your data on your
    device. <strong>This is a plain-language summary and a starting draft — please
    have it reviewed before relying on it.</strong>
  </p>

  <h2>Camera and video</h2>
  <p>
    TempoSeeker uses your camera to watch your putt and measure your stroke. Camera
    frames are analysed <strong>on your iPhone</strong> to calculate tempo, ball speed,
    distance and direction. Frames are <strong>never recorded, saved as video, or
    uploaded</strong> to us or any third party.
  </p>

  <h2>Information you provide</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Profile:</strong> a player name, and optionally an email address, used only to set up your profile in the app.</li>
    <li><strong>Putt and session data:</strong> your measured results and statistics are stored on your device so the app can show your history and trends.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Purchases</h2>
  <p>
    Subscriptions are processed by Apple through the App Store. We do not receive or
    store your payment card details. Apple's handling of your purchase is governed by
    Apple's privacy policy.
  </p>

  <h2>Analytics</h2>
  <p>
    The current version of this site and app does not run third-party analytics or
    advertising trackers. If we add privacy-respecting analytics in future, we will
    update this policy first.
  </p>

  <h2>What we don't do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>We do not sell your personal information.</li>
    <li>We do not upload or store your putting videos.</li>
    <li>We do not share your data with advertisers.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>TempoSeeker is not directed to children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect their information.</p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>We may update this policy as the app evolves. Material changes will be reflected here with a new "last updated" date.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions about privacy? Email <a href={`mailto:${site.supportEmail}`}>{site.supportEmail}</a>.</p>
</Legal>
